description: From Latin obducere, obductum; ob (see ob-) + ducere (“to lead”).

verbs.description: obduce (third-person singular simple present obduces, present participle obducing, simple past and past participle obduced)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To draw over, as a covering.
examples: Animal exhibits its Face in the native colour of its Skin but Man;  all others are covered with Feathers, or Hair, or a Cortex that is obduced over the Cutis  as in Elephants and some sort of Indian Dogs.
